        "text": "*[Bug 19077] New: `windows()` MouseUp event handling doesn't report which button was released*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19077>\n\n            Bug ID: 19077\n           Summary: `windows()` MouseUp event handling doesn't report\n                    which button was released\n           Product: R\n           Version: R-devel (trunk)\n          Hardware: Other\n                OS: Linux\n            Status: UNCONFIRMED\n          Severity: normal\n          Priority: P5\n         Component: Graphics\n          Assignee: <mailto:R-core@R-project.org|R-core@R-project.org>\n          Reporter: <mailto:trevor.l.davis@gmail.com|trevor.l.davis@gmail.com>\n\nAs documented in this [17684\ncomment](<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=17684#c4>) `windows()`\nMouseUp event handler doesn't report which mouse button was released.  This is\nin direct contrast with `x11()` whose MouseUp event handler does report this.\n\nThis [17684 comment](<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=17684#c3>)\nprovides code that lets you test what mouse buttons are reported in various\n`windows()` or `x11()` (depending where you run it) event handlers including\nthe MouseUp event handler.\n\nNote besides testing in Windows this bug can also be verified from Linux with\nthe help of the `wine64` emulator\n\n```\nwget <https:\/\/cran.r-project.org\/bin\/windows\/base\/R-devel-win.exe>\nwine64 R-devel-win.exe \/SILENT\nwine64 \"C:\/Program Files\/R\/R-devel\/bin\/x64\/R.exe\" --vanilla\n# run `windows()` and the code in the 17684 comment\n```\n\nI plan to upload a patch that fixes this soon.",
